name: Roy Cooper
tweet: In what could be @StanleyCup Finals pairing, our @Canes shut out the @Avalanche last night. Preseason goalie moves by Waddell look brilliant. Remember the doubts in July when we had signed no goalies? Come on. Admit it.

name: Roy Cooper
tweet: Another impressive win by our @Canes against the @NHL Bruins tonight. Wouldn’t have mattered if the Lamborghini Marchand @Bmarch63 had played. His cheap shots last night will give him a lot more time to post pretentious, misleading smaller hockey market tripe anyway.

name: Roy Cooper
tweet: Cheri Beasley is honest and trustworthy and she’ll put in the hard work necessary to fight for the people of North Carolina.  Please join me in making sure @CheriBeasleyNC can take on Washington as our next U.S. Senator.

name: Roy Cooper
tweet: Honored to be elected as new @DemGovs Chair. Governors are the last line of defense and the first chance for progress. Looking forward to putting wins on the board in 2022!

name: Roy Cooper
tweet: I don’t much like singular names for sports teams. Heat, Avalanche, Lightning, etc. The Kraken? I like it. A lot. Still, our @Canes gotta slay that monster tonight and bring in 9 out of 10 points so far on this fantastic wild west road trip.

name: Roy Cooper
tweet: It’s nice to win it twice. Go @Canes!

name: Roy Cooper
tweet: First time all year @Canes are down by 2 in a game. No matter. Make that 9 wins in a row.

name: Roy Cooper
tweet: Congratulations to Governor @PhilMurphyNJ on his re-election. We know how much real leadership in tough times matters and I look forward to continuing to work together to elect strong Governors who will fight to protect everyday people.

name: Roy Cooper
tweet: When will the 5-0-0 @Canes lose? Thursday win would be the best start ever. Lord Stanley material here. So early. But yes, I said it.

name: Roy Cooper
tweet: The @hornets with a fetching 4-1 start with only loss in OT. Great for Charlotte. Ball can ball, and this is a fun, exciting team with multiple weapons.

tweet: A lot has happened in the world since our last March 28th wedding anniversary and I am still blessed to have your love, support and friendship. Lucky me. Happy Anniversary Kristin.
